  h3 Blog #6 - 7/30 Insect Damage
  h6 By Alex Jerdee

  p After a few weeks with our hydroponic system and in soil planting, it became clear that not everything was going according to plan. Many of our turnip leaves had curving white trails in them, and we weren’t exactly sure where they came from. With some research, we realized that the trail was caused by leaf miners, whose larvae bore through the inside of the leaf. The leaf miners themselves are flies. The thought of maggots in our plants was horrifying, so looked for ways to address the issue.
